definitions.definition: ( uncountable ) Money in the form of notes or bills and coins , as opposed to checks , credit or electronic transactions .
examples: After you bounced those checks last time, they want to be paid in cash .

definitions.definition: ( uncountable , finance ) Liquid assets , money that can be traded quickly, as distinct from assets that are invested and cannot be easily exchanged .
( countable , Canada ) Cash register , or the counter in a business where the cash register is located.
examples: Let me just bring these to the cash for you.

definitions.definition: ( countable , gambling ) An instance of winning a cash prize.
( countable , archaic ) A place where money is kept, or where it is deposited and paid out; a money box.

definitions.definition: The low - denomination coin of southern India until 1818.
Any of several similar coins in Southeast and East Asia , particularly the imperial Chinese copper coin .
